Subject:[CT Birds] Vespers- Allen's Meadow
Just made a quick pass thru AM post rain at 5pm and had 3 VESPER SPARROWS on the short grass/mixed gravel area flanking the east side of the community gardens. A dozen+ WHITE-CROWNED SPARROWS and a mix of others. PINE SISKINS feeding in the gardens, with Pileated Woodpecker and a pair of Wood Ducks flying over. WINTER WREN calling from woodland edge. 
Joe Bear
Wilton 

